net.objectzoo.events

Interface Event2<T1,T2>

  • Type Parameters:
    T1 - The type of the first information parameter the event provides
    T2 - The type of the second information parameter the event provides
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Event2AsyncDelegate<T1,T2>, Event2Delegate<T1,T2>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Event2AsyncAdapter, Event2Caller, Event2Distributor

    public interface Event2<T1,T2>
    An Event2 is a source of signals and/or information that can be observed by subscribing BiConsumer instances to it. When an Event2 signals all subscribed BiConsumers are invoked. The order of of the invocation of the BiConsumers and the behavior in case of an RuntimeException during the invocation of a BiConsumer depends on the concrete Event2 implementation.
    Author:
    tilmann
